1 About

1.1 Models

Model Variance-covariance Restrictions on parameters Comment
(0) TwoRE \(\sigma^2_{g} A + \sigma^2_{ge} \begin{pmatrix} A_{1,1} & 0\\ 0 & A_{2,2} \end{pmatrix} + \sigma_{e}^2 I\) \(\rho_g \geq 0\) (Sul et al. 2016)
(1) smk0 \(\begin{pmatrix} \sigma_{e1}^2 I & 0 \\ 0 & \sigma_{e2}^2 I \end{pmatrix}\) Heterogeneity in errors
(2) arm \(\sigma_{g}^2 A + \sigma_{e}^2 I\)
(3) arm_smk0 \(\sigma_{g}^2 A + \begin{pmatrix} \sigma_{e1}^2 I & 0 \\ 0 & \sigma_{e2}^2 I \end{pmatrix}\)
(4) arm_by_smk \(\begin{pmatrix} \sigma_{g1}^2 A & \rho_g \sigma_{g1} \sigma_{g2} A\\ \rho_g \sigma_{g1} \sigma_{g2} A & \sigma_{g2}^2 A \end{pmatrix} + \begin{pmatrix} \sigma_{e1}^2 I & 0 \\ 0 & \sigma_{e2}^2 I \end{pmatrix}\) Complete model (Blangero 2009)
(5) arm_by_smk_vareq \(\sigma^2_{g} \begin{pmatrix} A & \rho_g A\\ \rho_g A & A \end{pmatrix} + \begin{pmatrix} \sigma_{e1}^2 I & 0 \\ 0 & \sigma_{e2}^2 I \end{pmatrix}\) \(\sigma_{g1} = \sigma_{g2} = \sigma_{g}\) Almost the same as (0) TwoRE
(6) arm_by_smk_rho1 \(\begin{pmatrix} \sigma_{g1}^2 A & \sigma_{g1} \sigma_{g2} A\\ \sigma_{g1} \sigma_{g2} A & \sigma_{g2}^2 A \end{pmatrix} + \begin{pmatrix} \sigma_{e1}^2 I & 0 \\ 0 & \sigma_{e2}^2 I \end{pmatrix}\) \(\rho_g = 1\)
(7) arm_by_smk_rho0 \(\begin{pmatrix} \sigma_{g1}^2 A & 0\\ 0 & \sigma_{g2}^2 A \end{pmatrix} + \begin{pmatrix} \sigma_{e1}^2 I & 0 \\ 0 & \sigma_{e2}^2 I \end{pmatrix}\) \(\rho_g = 0\)

Notes on the models

  1. For model (0) TwoRE, the genetic correlation is \(\rho_g = \sigma^2_{ge} / (\sigma^2_{g} + \sigma^2_{ge})\) and it is always non-negative.
    • The other model (4) arm_by_smk allows for negative values of \(\rho_g\).
  2. Models (5)-(6) are the null models for the main model (4) arm_by_smk.
  3. Is the model (4) arm_by_smk able to estimate correctly `rho_g$?
    • What is interpretation of negative values?

1.2 Summary of results

Marginal scans

  • When incorporating the heterogeneity of residual errors, smk0 models
    • More variance is explained and, thus, the attenuation of the signals is observed (more power).
    • The inflation is on the same level.
  • By adding an additional random term to describe the genetic heterogeneity, arm_by_smk model
    • Overfitting and some loss of power

Interaction scans

  • Incorporating the heterogeneity of residual errors into TwoRE model removes the most of inflation.

1.3 TODO

  • We need to incorporate the LRT to select between TwoRE and arm_by_smk models.
    • We observe empirically that arm_by_smk decreases the inflation from 1.19 to 1.05 for FEV1_FVC1 trait.
    • Though, arm_by_smk increases the inflation from 1.09 to 1.14 for FEV1pp trait.
    • See the last figure in the report.
